Ignoring allegations of misconduct and fraud, that's what the Mail and Guardian is accusing Sassa CEO Busisiwe "Totsie" Memela-Khambula of. It says she turned a blind eye to a R45.6-million cleaning tender in the Eastern Cape that was allegedly a jobs-for-pals situation. eNCA's Dan Moyane speaks to her for more. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - An over R45-million Sassa cleaning tender in the Eastern Cape, that was allegedly awarded to relatives, has been suspended. This after the Mail & Guardian reported that Sassa CEO, Busisiwe Memela-Khambula was turning a blind eye to the alleged misconduct and suspected fraud. READ: Sassa apologises for grant delays Memela-Khambula spoke to eNCA in the video above.